{"author":{"id":"a1ea83892e62ddf2114983880dd811fc8f472fda4507e17dd770341820e892f1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1715004650,"nonce":"ds9Eh3ZhbQXLCkmUhTEtmDdFmqw=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s588DM-","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5988#issuecomment-2096116542"},"message":"Hi @renu-pal, planemo will use the conda env you have locally on your machine, if the version is not bumped, to use the new env, that hopefully has the new version of r-glmmtmb you need to manually remove the conda env, e.g. use \n```\nconda env list\n```\nLook for something like: `__maaslin2@1.16.0             /home/paul/miniconda3/envs/__maaslin2@1.16.0`\n\nRemove that env with: `conda remove --name __maaslin2@1.16.0 --all`\nThen run planemo again and it should be build with the new  r-glmmtmb release\n\nNow that I think about it, how can one get the newest biocontainer in such as case ? I guess for this we need to bump the build number ? @bernt-matthias ?","files":null}]}